%h2 Submitting a Communication on Progress (COP)

%div{:class => "tab_container top_tabs", :style => 'width: 60%;'}
  %ul.tab_nav
    %li <a href="#introduction">Introduction</a>
    - if current_user.submit_grace_letter?
      %li <a href="#grace">Grace Letter</a>

  #introduction.tab_content
    %p.cop_description{:style => 'margin-top: 10px;'} As a participant in Global Compact LEAD, you have committed to communicate progress on implementing the Blueprint for Corporate Sustainability Leadership.
    %p.cop_description
      Please click the link below to Publish your COP.
      - if current_user.submit_grace_letter?
        Select the "Grace Letter" tab if you need to submit a grace letter for a 90 day extension to your COP deadline.
    %p= link_to 'Publish your COP', new_admin_organization_communication_on_progress_path(current_user.organization.id, :type_of_cop => 'lead'), :class => 'new_page_large'

  #grace.tab_content
    %h3 Request a COP due date extension

    %p.cop_description== In cases where companies foresee a delay in their communication, the Global Compact Office may grant a grace period of #{Organization::COP_GRACE_PERIOD} days if a reasonable explanation for the delay is posted on the Global Compact website, including an expected date of COP submission.

    - if current_user.submit_grace_letter?
      %p= link_to 'New Grace Letter', new_admin_organization_communication_on_progress_path(current_user.organization.id, :type_of_cop => 'grace'), :class => 'new_page_large'
    - else
      %p.cop_description
        %strong This option is not available because you have already submitted a Grace Letter.
